                            The Sacred Art of Diya Making
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-body text-text-secondary mb-6">
                            For over 2,000 years, the humble clay diya has been more than just a lamp. During Diwali, millions of these hand-crafted vessels illuminate homes across India, each one representing the triumph of light over darkness, knowledge over ignorance.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-body text-text-secondary mb-6">
                            Master potter Shyam Lal from Uttar Pradesh explains: "When I shape the clay, I'm not just making a lamp. I'm creating a vessel for prayers, hopes, and the divine light that connects us all."
